This paper focuses on deep reinforcement learning for robotic grasping, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also heavily utilizes machine learning techniques such as deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of off-policy learning and generalization, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
